SIMPLE: pollen
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pollen
<hw>Pol"len</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>pollen</ets>
fine flour, fine dust; cf. Gr. <?/]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Fine bran or
flour.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bailey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The fecundating dustlike cells of
the anthers of flowers. See <er>Flower</er>, and <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Filament</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pollen grain</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a particle
or call of pollen.</cd> -- <col><b>Pollen mass</b></col>, <cd>a
pollinium.</cd> <au>Gray.</au> -- <col><b>Pollen sac</b></col>, <cd>a
compartment of an anther containing pollen, -- usually there are four in
each anther.</cd> -- <col><b>Pollen tube</b></col>, <cd>a slender tube
which issues from the pollen grain on its contact with the stigma, which
it penetrates, thus conveying, it is supposed, the fecundating matter of
the grain to the ovule.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1109 --></p>

<p><ent>Pollenarious</ent>⟦br⟧
